command:
git add -A && git commit -m "$(cat <<'EOF'
Remove all project files except README

Clean slate for project restart.
EOF
)"

git commit -m "$(cat <<'EOF'
Document business requirements for contract manager

- Customers: Hubspot sync (inbound, read-only), local notes
- Products: CRM import + custom, variants, dependencies
- Contracts: Lifecycle states, primary/secondary, flexible terms
- Pricing: Multiple intervals, pro-rata, full price history
- Discounts: All types, combinations, customer agreements
- Price adjustments: Complex rules, hierarchical priority
- Auditing: Complete change tracking
- Users: Multi-tenant architecture, configurable roles
- Output: Reporting, exports, API with webhooks
EOF
)"

git add -A && git commit -m "$(cat <<'EOF'
Add architecture decisions and data model

Architecture:
- Multi-tenant: Shared schema with tenant_id
- Temporal data: Validity columns (valid_from/to)
- Audit log: Application level
- Contract versioning: Amendments
- Price calculation: Hybrid approach

Data model with 20+ entities covering:
- Tenant & Auth (Tenant, User, Role, AuditLog)
- Customers (Customer, CustomerNote, CustomerAgreement)
- Products (Product, ProductPrice, Categories, Variants, Dependencies, PriceLists)
- Contracts (Contract, ContractItem, ContractAmendment, ContractDocument)
- Discounts & Price Adjustments
- Notifications
EOF
)"

git add -A && git commit -m "$(cat <<'EOF'
Add implementation phases (MVP, Core, Extensions)

Phase 1 (MVP): Setup, Multi-tenant, Auth, Hubspot sync, 
Products, Contracts with retrospective entry, Audit log

Phase 2: Amendments, Discounts, Price history, 
Customer agreements, Dashboard, Primary/Secondary contracts

Phase 3: API/Webhooks, Price adjustments, PDF, 
Notifications, Documents, Export, Magic Link
EOF
)"

git add -A && git commit -m "$(cat <<'EOF'
Add UI fundamentals

- Shadcn/ui + Preline + Tailwind CSS
- Classic layout: Sidebar + Content
- Desktop-first
- Global + contextual search
- Tables with sort/filter/pagination
- Wizard-based forms
- i18n ready (DE + EN)
EOF
)"
